    Function: Set screen width and length
    Syntax:   SCREEN [WIDTH = width] [LENGTH = length]

    ...If neither WIDTH nor LENGTH is specified, you will see current
       settings.

    Examples:

    SCREEN  W = 80  L=22
    ...sets screen width to 80 columns and length to 22 lines

    SCREEN  W 40
    ...sets screen width to 40 columns

    SCREEN
    ...displays Width and Length settings
